# Prometheus `basic_auth.password_file` for scraping the ADMIN-gated /actuator/prometheus (M5).
#
# Copy this file to `metrics_pw` (no extension) in this directory and replace the placeholder below
# with the RAW admin password - i.e. the PASSWORD half (everything after the first ':') of
# THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH - with NO trailing newline:
#
#   printf '%s' "${THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH#*:}" > metrics_pw
#
# The USERNAME (the half BEFORE the ':') is non-secret and lives inline as `basic_auth.username` in
# prometheus.yml (default "admin"); it MUST match THEBULLPEN_ADMIN_BASIC_AUTH's user-half. The real
# `metrics_pw` is gitignored; only this `.example` is committed. The secrets dir is mounted read-only
# at /etc/prometheus/secrets (see infra/docker-compose.yml).
#
# NOTE: this is the RAW password, NOT base64("user:password") - `basic_auth.password_file` wants the
# plaintext password (this replaced the old `metrics_authz` base64 file, which used the INVALID
# `authorization: {type: Basic}` block that crash-looped the 2026-06-24 cutover). Comment lines are
# fine here because Prometheus never reads `.example`, only the real `metrics_pw`, which must contain
# ONLY the password string.
REPLACE_WITH_RAW_ADMIN_PASSWORD
